Lim Si Pin (simplified Chinese: 林时彬; traditional Chinese: 林時彬; pinyin: Lín Shíbīn) is a Malaysian politician. He ever served as the head of the youth wing of Parti Gerakan Rakyat Malaysia (Gerakan), a component party of Barisan Nasional (BN) coalition; from 2008 to 2011.Lim is the son of Lim Keng Yaik, a former cabinet minister and president of Gerakan.He contested the Malaysian General Election 2008 for the Barisan Nasional held parliamentary seat of Batu, Kuala Lumpur, but was defeated by Tian Chua of the opposition People's Justice Party (PKR).


